description: This file implements the foundational functions for a CCSP CWMP Stun Manager object, including creation, initialization, object enrollment, and removal functions. It structures the setup of stun interface components and manages their lifecycle within the CCSP framework.

classes.name: CCSP_CWMP_STUN_MANAGER_OBJECT
classes.description: Main object structure representing the CCSP CWMP Stun Manager with function pointers and properties for managing STUN communications.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE CcspCwmpStunmoCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs and initializes a new CCSP CWMP Stun Manager object, setting up its function pointers and internal components.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS CcspCwmpStunmoRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Cleans up and deletes the CCSP CWMP Stun Manager object, freeing associated resources.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS CcspCwmpStunmoEnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Allocates and associates internal components such as the STUN interface and simple client objects needed by the manager.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS CcspCwmpStunmoInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes member variables, sets up function pointers, and prepares the object for operation.
